moves.name: Fake Out
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to make the target flinch. Fails unless it is the user's first turn on the field.
moves.shortDesc: Hits first. First turn out only. 100% flinch chance.

moves.name: Parting Shot
moves.desc: Lowers the target's Attack and Special Attack by 1 stage. If this move is successful, the user switches out even if it is trapped and is replaced immediately by a selected party member. The user does not switch out if the target's Attack and Special Attack stat stages were both unchanged, or if there are no unfainted party members.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers target's Atk, Sp. Atk by 1. User switches.

moves.name: Snarl
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to lower the target's Special Attack by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 100% chance to lower the foe(s) Sp. Atk by 1.

moves.name: Icy Wind
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to lower the target's Speed by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 100% chance to lower the foe(s) Speed by 1.

moves.name: Foul Play
moves.desc: Damage is calculated using the target's Attack stat, including stat stage changes. The user's Ability, item, and burn are used as normal.
moves.shortDesc: Uses target's Attack stat in damage calculation.

moves.name: Knock Off
moves.desc: If the target is holding an item that can be removed from it, ignoring the Sticky Hold Ability, this move's power is multiplied by 1.5. If the user has not fainted, the target loses its held item. This move cannot cause Pokemon with the Sticky Hold Ability to lose their held item or cause a Kyogre, a Groudon, a Giratina, an Arceus, a Genesect, a Silvally, a Zacian, or a Zamazenta to lose their Blue Orb, Red Orb, Griseous Orb, Plate, Drive, Memory, Rusted Sword, or Rusted Shield respectively. Items lost to this move cannot be regained with Recycle or the Harvest Ability.
moves.shortDesc: 1.5x damage if foe holds an item. Removes item.

moves.name: Protect
moves.desc: The user is protected from most attacks made by other Pokemon during this turn. This move has a 1/X chance of being successful, where X starts at 1 and triples each time this move is successfully used. X resets to 1 if this move fails, if the user's last move used is not Baneful Bunker, Burning Bulwark, Detect, Endure, King's Shield, Max Guard, Obstruct, Protect, Quick Guard, Silk Trap, Spiky Shield, or Wide Guard, or if it was one of those moves and the user's protection was broken. Fails if the user moves last this turn.
moves.shortDesc: Prevents moves from affecting the user this turn.

moves.name: Helping Hand
moves.desc: The power of the target's attack this turn is multiplied by 1.5 (this effect is stackable). Fails if there is no ally adjacent to the user or if the ally already moved this turn, but does not fail if the ally is using a two-turn move.
moves.shortDesc: One adjacent ally's move power is 1.5x this turn.

moves.name: Feint
moves.desc: If this move is successful, it breaks through the target's Baneful Bunker, Detect, King's Shield, Protect, or Spiky Shield for this turn, allowing other Pokemon to attack the target normally. If the target's side is protected by Crafty Shield, Mat Block, Quick Guard, or Wide Guard, that protection is also broken for this turn and other Pokemon may attack the target's side normally.
moves.shortDesc: Nullifies Detect, Protect, and Quick/Wide Guard.

moves.name: Taunt
moves.desc: Prevents the target from using non-damaging moves for its next three turns. Pokemon with the Oblivious Ability or protected by the Aroma Veil Ability are immune.
moves.shortDesc: Target can't use status moves its next 3 turns.

moves.name: Chilling Water
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to lower the target's Attack by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 100% chance to lower the target's Attack by 1.

moves.name: Thunder Wave
moves.desc: Paralyzes the target. This move does not ignore type immunity.
moves.shortDesc: Paralyzes the target.

moves.name: Hypnosis
moves.desc: Causes the target to fall asleep.
moves.shortDesc: Causes the target to fall asleep.

moves.name: Screech
moves.desc: Lowers the target's Defense by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the target's Defense by 2.

moves.name: Quash
moves.desc: Causes the target to take its turn after all other Pokemon this turn, no matter the priority of its selected move. Fails if the target already moved this turn.
moves.shortDesc: Forces the target to move last this turn.

moves.name: U-turn
moves.desc: If this move is successful and the user has not fainted, the user switches out even if it is trapped and is replaced immediately by a selected party member. The user does not switch out if there are no unfainted party members, or if the target switched out using an Eject Button or through the effect of the Emergency Exit or Wimp Out Abilities.
moves.shortDesc: User switches out after damaging the target.

moves.name: Thunderbolt
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to paralyze the target.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to paralyze the target.

moves.name: Switcheroo
moves.desc: The user swaps its held item with the target's held item. Fails if either the user or the target is holding a Mail or Z-Crystal, if neither is holding an item, if the user is trying to give or take a Mega Stone to or from the species that can Mega Evolve with it, or if the user is trying to give or take a Blue Orb, a Red Orb, a Griseous Orb, a Plate, a Drive, or a Memory to or from a Kyogre, a Groudon, a Giratina, an Arceus, a Genesect, or a Silvally, respectively. The target is immune to this move if it has the Sticky Hold Ability.
moves.shortDesc: User switches its held item with the target's.

moves.name: Trailblaze
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to raise the user's Speed by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 100% chance to raise the user's Speed by 1.

moves.name: Psych Up
moves.desc: The user copies all of the target's current stat stage changes.
moves.shortDesc: Copies the target's current stat stages.

moves.name: Assurance
moves.desc: Power doubles if the target has already taken damage this turn, other than direct damage from Belly Drum, confusion, Curse, or Pain Split.
moves.shortDesc: Power doubles if target was damaged this turn.

moves.name: Fury Swipes
moves.desc: Hits two to five times. Has a 35% chance to hit two or three times and a 15% chance to hit four or five times. If one of the hits breaks the target's substitute, it will take damage for the remaining hits. If the user has the Skill Link Ability, this move will always hit five times.
moves.shortDesc: Hits 2-5 times in one turn.

moves.name: Dark Pulse
moves.desc: Has a 20% chance to make the target flinch.
moves.shortDesc: 20% chance to make the target flinch.

moves.name: Nasty Plot
moves.desc: Raises the user's Special Attack by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Raises the user's Sp. Atk by 2.

moves.name: Sunny Day
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the weather becomes Sunny Day. The damage of Fire-type attacks is multiplied by 1.5 and the damage of Water-type attacks is multiplied by 0.5 during the effect. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Heat Rock. Fails if the current weather is Sunny Day.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, intense sunlight powers Fire moves.

moves.name: Play Rough
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to lower the target's Attack by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to lower the target's Attack by 1.

moves.name: Burning Jealousy
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to burn the target if it had a stat stage raised this turn.
moves.shortDesc: 100% burns a target that had a stat rise this turn.

moves.name: Swift
moves.desc: This move does not check accuracy.
moves.shortDesc: This move does not check accuracy. Hits foes.

moves.name: Gunk Shot
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to poison the target.
moves.shortDesc: 30% chance to poison the target.

moves.name: Fake Tears
moves.desc: Lowers the target's Special Defense by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the target's Sp. Def by 2.

moves.name: Charm
moves.desc: Lowers the target's Attack by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the target's Attack by 2.

moves.name: Flatter
moves.desc: Raises the target's Special Attack by 1 stage and confuses it.
moves.shortDesc: Raises the target's Sp. Atk by 1 and confuses it.

moves.name: Shadow Ball
moves.desc: Has a 20% chance to lower the target's Special Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 20% chance to lower the target's Sp. Def by 1.

moves.name: Hyper Voice
moves.desc: No additional effect.
moves.shortDesc: No additional effect. Hits adjacent foes.

moves.name: Endeavor
moves.desc: Deals damage to the target equal to (target's current HP - user's current HP). The target is unaffected if its current HP is less than or equal to the user's current HP.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the target's HP to the user's HP.

moves.name: Seed Bomb
moves.desc: No additional effect.
moves.shortDesc: No additional effect.

moves.name: Roar
moves.desc: The target is forced to switch out and be replaced with a random unfainted ally. Fails if the target is the last unfainted Pokemon in its party, or if the target used Ingrain previously or has the Suction Cups Ability.
moves.shortDesc: Forces the target to switch to a random ally.

moves.name: Power Gem
moves.desc: No additional effect.
moves.shortDesc: No additional effect.

moves.name: Thunder
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to paralyze the target. This move can hit a target using Bounce, Fly, or Sky Drop, or is under the effect of Sky Drop. If the weather is Primordial Sea or Rain Dance, this move does not check accuracy. If the weather is Desolate Land or Sunny Day, this move's accuracy is 50%. If this move is used against a Pokemon holding Utility Umbrella, this move's accuracy remains at 70%.
moves.shortDesc: 30% chance to paralyze. Can't miss in rain.

moves.name: Rest
moves.desc: The user falls asleep for the next two turns and restores all of its HP, curing itself of any non-volatile status condition in the process. Fails if the user has full HP, is already asleep, or if another effect is preventing sleep.
moves.shortDesc: User sleeps 2 turns and restores HP and status.

moves.name: Shadow Claw
moves.desc: Has a higher chance for a critical hit.
moves.shortDesc: High critical hit ratio.

moves.name: Facade
moves.desc: Power doubles if the user is burned, paralyzed, or poisoned. The physical damage halving effect from the user's burn is ignored.
moves.shortDesc: Power doubles if user is burn/poison/paralyzed.

moves.name: Amnesia
moves.desc: Raises the user's Special Defense by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Raises the user's Sp. Def by 2.

moves.name: Double-Edge
moves.desc: If the target lost HP, the user takes recoil damage equal to 33% the HP lost by the target, rounded half up, but not less than 1 HP.
moves.shortDesc: Has 33% recoil.

abilities.name: Technician
abilities.desc: This Pokemon's moves of 60 power or less have their power multiplied by 1.5, including Struggle. This effect comes after a move's effect changes its own power.
abilities.shortDesc: This Pokemon's moves of 60 power or less have 1.5x power, including Struggle.

abilities.name: Rattled
abilities.desc: This Pokemon's Speed is raised by 1 stage if hit by a Bug-, Dark-, or Ghost-type attack, or if an opposing Pokemon affected this Pokemon with the Intimidate Ability.
abilities.shortDesc: Speed is raised 1 stage if hit by a Bug-, Dark-, or Ghost-type attack, or Intimidated.

items.name: Sitrus Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/4 max HP when at 1/2 max HP or less. Single use.

items.name: Rocky Helmet
items.desc: If holder is hit by a contact move, the attacker loses 1/6 of its max HP.

items.name: Lagging Tail
items.desc: Holder moves last in its priority bracket.

items.name: Assault Vest
items.desc: Holder's Sp. Def is 1.5x, but it can only select damaging moves.

items.name: Iapapa Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -Def Nature. Single use.

items.name: Aguav Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -SpD Nature. Single use.

items.name: Focus Sash
items.desc: If holder's HP is full, will survive an attack that would KO it with 1 HP. Single use.

items.name: Mental Herb
items.desc: Cures holder of Attract, Disable, Encore, Heal Block, Taunt, Torment. Single use.

items.name: Leftovers
items.desc: At the end of every turn, holder restores 1/16 of its max HP.

items.name: Roseli Berry
items.desc: Halves damage taken from a supereffective Fairy-type attack. Single use.

items.name: Ring Target
items.desc: The holder's type immunities granted solely by its typing are negated.

items.name: Insect Plate
items.desc: Holder's Bug-type attacks have 1.2x power. Judgment is Bug type.

items.name: Life Orb
items.desc: Holder's attacks do 1.3x damage, and it loses 1/10 its max HP after the attack.

items.name: Black Glasses
items.desc: Holder's Dark-type attacks have 1.2x power.

items.name: Heavy-Duty Boots
items.desc: When switching in, the holder is unaffected by hazards on its side of the field.

items.name: Ability Shield
items.desc: Holder's Ability cannot be changed by any effect.

items.name: Choice Specs
items.desc: Holder's Sp. Atk is 1.5x, but it can only select the first move it executes.

items.name: Covert Cloak
items.desc: Holder is not affected by the secondary effect of another Pokemon's attack.

items.name: Bright Powder
items.desc: The accuracy of attacks against the holder is 0.9x.

items.name: Weakness Policy
items.desc: If holder is hit super effectively, raises Attack, Sp. Atk by 2 stages. Single use.

items.name: Wise Glasses
items.desc: Holder's special attacks have 1.1x power.

items.name: Safety Goggles
items.desc: Holder is immune to powder moves and damage from Sandstorm or Hail.

items.name: Throat Spray
items.desc: Raises holder's Special Attack by 1 stage after it uses a sound move. Single use.

items.name: Blunder Policy
items.desc: If the holder misses due to accuracy, its Speed is raised by 2 stages. Single use.

items.name: Choice Scarf
items.desc: Holder's Speed is 1.5x, but it can only select the first move it executes.

items.name: Mago Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -Spe Nature. Single use.

items.name: Normal Gem
items.desc: Holder's first successful Normal-type attack will have 1.3x power. Single use.

items.name: Dread Plate
items.desc: Holder's Dark-type attacks have 1.2x power. Judgment is Dark type.

items.name: Eject Button
items.desc: If holder survives a hit, it immediately switches out to a chosen ally. Single use.

items.name: Psychic Seed
items.desc: If the terrain is Psychic Terrain, raises holder's Sp. Def by 1 stage. Single use.

items.name: Figy Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -Atk Nature. Single use.

items.name: Wide Lens
items.desc: The accuracy of attacks by the holder is 1.1x.

items.name: Chesto Berry
items.desc: Holder wakes up if it is asleep. Single use.

items.name: Sticky Barb
items.desc: Each turn, holder loses 1/8 max HP. An attacker making contact can receive it.

items.name: Expert Belt
items.desc: Holder's attacks that are super effective against the target do 1.2x damage.

items.name: Power Bracer
items.desc: Holder's Speed is halved. The Klutz Ability does not ignore this effect.

items.name: Lum Berry
items.desc: Holder cures itself if it has a non-volatile status or is confused. Single use.

items.name: Red Card
items.desc: If holder survives a hit, attacker is forced to switch to a random ally. Single use.

items.name: Quick Claw
items.desc: Each turn, holder has a 20% chance to move first in its priority bracket.
